`scripts/` is the repo's collection of standalone CI/lint checks and doc-generation scripts, each independently invocable and each speaking ctx-verify's shared diagnostic protocol. Depending on this directory means running one script at a time via ctx-verify's batteries; there's no shared library code or importable module here — coupling is entirely at the protocol and convention level, not code.

Every check script (`cycle_check.sh`, `machete_check.sh`, `no_allow_check.sh`, `rationale_check.py`, `retired_terms_check.sh`, `workspace_lints_check.sh`) emits failures as `FAIL: path:line: message` lines to stderr and communicates pass/fail via exit code — this exact format is a hard contract with ctx-verify's `split_loc` parser; changing it in one script without checking the parser breaks that check silently. All enumerate files via `git ls-files` (tracked + untracked-not-ignored), never a filesystem walk, specifically to avoid racing `target/` writes and to get gitignore pruning for free — a new check script should follow this pattern rather than reinvent it.

The two generator scripts (`gen_readme_architecture.sh`, `gen_tool_contracts.sh`) share a different convention: `--write`/`--check` modes, fixed HTML-comment markers delimiting a generated block, and `awk`-based whole-block replacement. `gen_tool_contracts.sh` additionally requires `ctx-context`/`ctx-verify`/`ctx-scan`/`ctx-cage`/`ctx-brief` prebuilt in `target/debug/` — it never invokes cargo, so build ordering matters when wiring these into CI. `gen_readme_architecture.sh` is the one consumer of `.context/rollup.ctx` as a raw injected artifact rather than a `--contract` call.

`cycle_check.sh` and `rationale_check.py` are both explicit MVP placeholders deferring to future dylint rules (documented in docs/DYLINT_RULES.md); their checks are heuristic/partial, not the final enforcement mechanism. `retired_terms_check.sh` and the `BANNED` list are the enforcement side of the ADR deprecation process in docs/DECISIONS.md — new retirements require editing both that doc and this array.

No intent.md exists for this directory.